cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the problem of private computation of a sequence of linear functions, which involves information-theoretic aspects of privacy and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of multiple servers and their collaboration, which suggests the possibility of distributed computing and communication, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) likely categories as well. The paper also involves the study of capacity and achievability, which are related to information theory and communication complexity, respectively, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) possible categories.
